<TITLE> BDR arrest 1 arms smuggler </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Chapainawabganj, May 3 (bdnews24.com)  BDR men arrested an arms trader from Kiranganj border at Shibganj upazila in Chapainawabganj on Monday. The arrestee, Alauddin, 35, is the son of Kosimuddin of Kiranganj village. Major Nazrul Islam, operation officer of 39 Rifles Battalion in Chapainawabganj, said that a BDR team of Kiranganj BOP had arrested Alauddin at around 1pm for possessing two pistols. Islam also said that Alauddin was an arms trader. He used to smuggle arms from India and sell them in Bangladesh. The BDR handed the detained over to Shibganj Police Station and also filed a case under the Arms Act. BDR had also seized a pistol, two magazines and five rounds of bullets from Akbarpur village of Shibganj upazila on May 1. bdnews24
